        <substitution method="pen" type="deletion" copyText="
            '' Your bait of falshood takes this carp of truth, |
            '' And thus do we of wisdom and of reach, |
            '' With windlesses, and with essays of byas, | 
            '' By indirectis find directions out: |
            '' So by my former Lecture and advice |
            '' Shall you my son. You have me, have you not? |
            '' Rey. My Lord I haue. |
            '' Pol. God buy you; fare you well. |
            '' Rey. Good my Lord. |
            '' Pol. Obserue his inclination in your selfe. |
            '' Rey. I shall my Lord. |
            '' Pol. And let him plye his Musicke. |
            '' Rey. Well, my Lord. Exit. |
            Enter Ophelia. |
            '' Pol. Farewell: |" amendedText="I could not this believe,"/>
        
